messages.content:
We want to review and improve this prompt: [[[You are an instructional-design expert creating Marp slides for the BEIT Solar Energy Training (Mosul, Iraq). Apply adult-learning best practices and the visual standards below.
User:
Task: Build a complete Marp markdown deck for Day 3 using the facilitator guide pasted after this prompt.
1 — Structure
Follow the day’s hour-by-hour agenda; dedicate at least one slide to each scheduled activity.
Sequence: Title → Objectives → Agenda overview → Activity slides → Daily review → Next-day preview.
Cap text at 5–7 bullets or ≤40 words per slide (except activity instructions).
2 — Content harvesting rules
• Pull key ideas from “What to Say,” “Steps,” “Stories,” and “Common Q&A.”
• Include financial examples only when they advance learning (e.g., ROI demo, price-comparison exercise).
• Hide trainer guidance and timing tips inside HTML comments (<!-- ... -->).
3 — Visual guidelines
Choose the simplest helpful visual per concept:
Diagram type	Ideal use-case	Mermaid starter tag
Flowchart TD	processes / decision paths	flowchart TD
Mindmap	categorising checklists	mindmap
Pie	proportions / cost splits	pie
QuadrantChart	2-axis comparisons	quadrantChart
ClassDiagram	hierarchies / part-of relationships	classDiagram
Timeline	schedules / trends	timeline
Use a diagram only if it clarifies learning; otherwise insert a relevant photo or simple icon. Keep ≤15 nodes, TD orientation where applicable.		
4 — Styling snippet (inject once at top)
marp: true
theme: default
paginate: true
backgroundColor: "#fafafa"
header: "Solar Energy System Design & Installation Training"
footer: "BEIT Project – Mosul, Iraq"
style: |
  img.mermaid-diagram {
    max-width: 85%;
    max-height: 450px;
    width: auto;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    margin: 0 auto;
    border-radius: 5px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    background-color: white;
    padding: 10px;
  }
  section { font-size: 30px; }
  h1 { color: #1e88e5; }
  h2 { color: #26a69a; }
5 — Output format
Start with the YAML header above.
Produce the slide content.]]]
Review the prompt and the attached image - it's working well except it's also generating slides with this sort of flowchart and the image is awkward and slide, how do we prevent it from making things like that. I want to keep makin gmermaid charts. So let's update the prompt to offer guidance on when/how to use which type of chart format to make sure it's appropriate. Also, let's modify the prompt to ensure it generates the output as a .md file and to be able to download it as an md artifact immediately. Update the prompt and then run it for day 4 attached to test it out.

